  "security_notes": "control.exe is a system-binary proxy through Control Panel files (T1218.002). Because a `.cpl` is a DLL, an attacker delivers one (often renamed to look like a document) and has control.exe load and run it under a trusted, signed Microsoft process, bypassing application-control rules that allow control.exe. Malicious `.cpl` files have been a recurring malware delivery format for exactly this reason.\n\nSince loading a legitimate applet is normal, the context is what matters: a `.cpl` from a temp or download folder, a parent like an Office application, or control.exe spawning a shell, mark it as abuse rather than someone opening a settings page.\n",
